		<t>
            <field>DirectPaymentFlag</field>
            <desc>
                <p>This flag is set on the credit party and it is used to denote the receiver of the MT103 payment message when cover method is used.</p>
				<p>This flag is set only when a cover method of routing is used.</p> 
				<p>The DirectPaymentFlag can also be used to determine if a cover method of routing is used for the payment or not. </p>
				<p>However, the DirectPaymentFlag is set at a credit party level and not at a transaction level.</p>				
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
                <p>1 alphanumeric character</p>
				<p>Possible values:</p>	
				<p>Y - Credit Party is the receiver of the MT103 message when cover method is used.</p>
				<p>N or Blank - Credit party is not the receiver of the MT103 message.</p>
            </desc>
